Package: doublethink
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: secure pub/sub broker, ntfy-easy with genuinely private channels
 doublethink is a publish/subscribe message broker that is as easy to stand up as
 ntfy, but with real authentication and genuinely private channels. ntfy is
 effortless because its topic name is the only gate; doublethink keeps that ease
 and adds the thing ntfy omits: identity and private channels you can trust with
 real traffic.
 .
 Private channels admit only authenticated, authorised parties (Ed25519
 challenge/response; knowing a channel name grants no access), and their payloads
 are end-to-end encrypted between the paired peers so the broker operator never
 sees plaintext. Pairing is man-in-the-middle resistant via single-use invite
 codes and an out-of-band short authentication string. Opt-in plaintext public
 topics are available ntfy-style for those who want them. Delivery is
 bidirectional, asynchronous, and streaming.
 .
 DISCLAIMER: doublethink carries other parties' private traffic and enforces
 access to it. It is provided AS IS, WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. You alone are
 responsible for how you deploy and secure it and for the data that flows through
 it. The author is not liable for any harm, data loss, data exposure, or security
 incident, however caused. No security mechanism is perfect. See
 /usr/share/doc/doublethink/README.md for the full disclaimer.
